# 🧪 Cartlow Automation Testing (TestNG + Selenium)

This project automates testing for the [Cartlow](https://cartlow.com) eCommerce website using **Selenium WebDriver**, **TestNG**, and **ExtentReports**.  
It performs a full flow — from login to checkout — and generates a detailed HTML report.

---

## 🧰 Tech Used
- Java  
- Selenium WebDriver  
- TestNG  
- ExtentReports  
- WebDriverManager  
- ChromeDriver  

---

## ⚙️ How It Works
The tests cover:
1. Login to Cartlow website  
2. Change the region to UAE  
3. Search for laptop and smartwatch  
4. Add both to the cart  
5. Verify items exist in the cart  
6. Remove an item from the cart  
7. Continue to checkout  
8. Generate test report (**CartlowReport.html**)  

---

## 📁 Project Structure
Algoriza_automation_project/
│
├── CartlowTest.java
├── CartlowReport.html # Generated after running tests
└── README.md


---

## ▶️ How to Run
1. Clone the project  
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/Algoriza_automation_project.git


Open it in IntelliJ IDEA or Eclipse

Make sure dependencies are in your pom.xml (Maven):

<dependencies>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>
        <artifactId>selenium-java</artifactId>
        <version>4.23.0</version>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>io.github.bonigarcia</groupId>
        <artifactId>webdrivermanager</artifactId>
        <version>5.8.0</version>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.testng</groupId>
        <artifactId>testng</artifactId>
        <version>7.10.0</version>
        <scope>test</scope>
    </dependency>
    <dependency>
        <groupId>com.aventstack</groupId>
        <artifactId>extentreports</artifactId>
        <version>5.1.1</version>
    </dependency>
</dependencies>


Run tests with:

Right-click the file → Run 'CartlowTest'

or via command:

mvn test

🧾 Report

After test execution, a report named:

CartlowReport.html


will be generated in the project root.
Open it in a browser to view the full test summary.

